{"lemma":"نَكَباتِ","slug":"نَكَباتِ","root":"ن.ك.ب","root_slug":"ن-ك-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ن-ك-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n40449","n40453","n40454"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%86%D9%8E%D9%83%D9%8E%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"catastrophe, disaster"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"the expulsion of Palestinian Arabs from most of Mandatory Palestine and the destruction of their homes in 1948","tags":["specifically"],"examples":[{"text":"النَّكْبَة","english":"the Nakba"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"failure, fiasco"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Instance noun of نَكَبَ (nakaba, “to afflict, distress”)."},"ipa":["/nak.ba/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n40449","headword_ar":"نِكّبه","root":"nkb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tanokiybN","text_ar":"تَنْكِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He removed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"put aside,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"out of the way, him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it."},{"kind":"text","text":"Thus it is both trans. and intrans. (K.) See 1. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nak~ibohu Ean~aA","text_ar":"نَكِّبْهُ عَنَّا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Put him away from us; put him out of our way."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n40453","headword_ar":"نَكْبَةٌ","root":"nkb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A hurt"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the foot"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by a stone, causing a bleeding:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a hit by a stone"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the foot"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. Ex."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layosa duwna h`*aA AlA^amori nakobapN walaA *ub~aAHN","text_ar":"لَيْسَ دُونَ هٰذَا الاَمْرِ نَكْبَةٌ وَلَا ذُبَّاحٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There is not in the way of the attainment of this thing a hurt"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the foot"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by a stone, &c., nor a crack in the inside of the foot."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, ISd.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*b~AH","text_ar":"ذبّاح"},{"kind":"text","text":".] Hence"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nakobapN","text_ar":"نَكْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense immediately following. (TA.) ―         -b2-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A misfortune; an evil accident; a disaster; an affliction; a calamity:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA:) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nakobN","text_ar":"نَكْبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) pl. of the former"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nakabAatN","text_ar":"نَكَباَتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) and of the latter,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nukuwbN","text_ar":"نُكُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n40454","headword_ar":"نُكْبَةٌ","root":"nkb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A heap of corn, not measured nor weighed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuborapN","text_ar":"صُبْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}